7.text: When he went to the bus stop his friends were not to be seen.

8.text: “Oh no! It looks like the school bus has already left. Maybe I can catch the next bus.”

9.text: The bus wasn’t crowded as it usually is. Hasmal thought to himself. Within a few minutes, he was in school. He looked around. There was nobody.

10.text: “Where are the students? Where are the prefects who are generally here in the morning?” Hasmal was baffled.

11.text: He thought of going for the morning assembly in the playground.

12.text: “But there is a group of girls playing netball in the playground. Where are the students in our school? Why is it quiet today?” Hasmal thought.

13.text: He thought of going to his classroom to keep his bag. But oh, it was locked. He tried to open it but he couldn’t. Just then the school security guard was passing by.

14.text: “Excuse me! Why are you in your uniform today?”

15.text: 1. What time did Hasmal wake up? 2. What did he do after he woke up? 3. What was unusual about this day? 4. What would have happened if he had talked to his mother in the

16.text: morning? 5. Give a suitable ending to the story.
